text: Going to church with your friends is refreshing because only there you get to see everybody absolutely serious. In day-to-day everyday life everyone is a jokester, nothing is grave, it's all humor, idle chatter. But at Liturgy everyone is serious, silent. Your soul is the stakes.

Liturgy is the brief hour when clarity is absolute and all illusions and comedies fade out. Everybody is very, very serious. You get to see the people you love as they are. Life as it truly is. Everyone is realized, fulfilled in his role. Nothing else compares in a pure realness.
As always I invite all my friends here to visit a local Orthodox Liturgy on Sunday morning
